## Requirements

- Add focused tests for config parsing, secret handling, provider selection, OAuth token refresh logic, and any request-header construction introduced for Codex support.
- Document setup and limitations in user-facing docs, including callback port `1455`, manual pasteback fallback, and expected model naming/config examples.
- Update any quickstart/configuration references that currently imply OpenAI support is API-key only.

## Acceptance Criteria

- Automated tests cover the new auth mode and runtime routing behavior.
- Docs show at least one end-to-end Codex subscription configuration example.
- `make test` passes after the implementation lands.
